Basic TCP chat server written in Java.

Requirments:
  Client Side:
  Done - can connect, disconnect and reconnect to the server.
  Done - can send messages to the server.
  Done - can recieve messages from other clients.
  Removed from scope - can request message history.
  Server Side:
  Removed from scope - save client messages.
  Done - relay messages to all connected clients.
  Done - track connected clients.
  CLI functions:
  Removed from scope - list connected clients.
  Done - connect / disconnect to server.
  Removed from scope - clear chat.
  Removed from scope - retrieve chat history (10/25/50/100 messages).

Possible enhancements:
  - chat rooms
  - private chat

  Scope was reduced. main project goal was to learn about TCP and Threads.
